    "about": "Recruiters: I am not interested in opportunities unless you represent Tim Schafer or Ron Gilbert. Here is my body of work: https://foxchickengrain.com/\n\n# OpenAI\n\n* Tech lead for Codex CLI https://github.com/openai/codex\n\n# Facebook\n\n* 2024 DotSlash https://engineering.fb.com/2024/02/06/developer-tools/dotslash-simplified-executable-deployment/\n* 2023 CodeCompose, GenAI-assisted code authoring https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ANDJ0TKjyWw\n* 2022 Open sourced Sapling, source control client https://engineering.fb.com/2022/11/15/open-source/sapling-source-control-scalable/\n* 2022 Launched ReviewStack, GitHub pull request UI that supports stacked changes https://reviewstack.dev/\n* 2020-2021 Internal web-based tools for code browsing, search, and project management\n* 2019 Miscellaneous work to promote Rust internally at Facebook\n* 2016-2018 Founding member of EdenFS team, the virtual filesystem component of Sapling https://github.com/facebook/sapling\n* 2014-2015 Created Nuclide (https://engineering.fb.com/2015/06/23/developer-tools/building-nuclide-a-unified-developer-experience), a set of packages that provide IDE-like functionality for Atom (https://atom.io/). This work was later ported to VS Code.\n* 2012-2013 Created Buck (https://github.com/facebook/buck), an open source build tool. Its use at Meta has recently been superseded by Buck2: https://engineering.fb.com/2023/04/06/open-source/buck2-open-source-large-scale-build-system/\n\n# Independent\n\n* Wrote Closure: The Definitive Guide (O'Reilly, 2010).\n* Created plovr (plovr.com), a Closure build tool.\n\n# Google\n\n* Worked on the frontend of Google Calendar (https://calendar.google.com/calendar/) and Google Tasks (https://mail.google.com/tasks/desktop).\n* Built the Closure Compiler Application Service (http://closure-compiler.appspot.com/home).\n* Helped open source the Closure Tools (https://developers.google.com/closure/).\n\n# MIT\n\n* MEng Thesis: End-User Programming for the Web (http://bolinfest.com/Michael_Bolin_Thesis_Chickenfoot.pdf).\n* Created Chickenfoot (http://up.csail.mit.edu/chickenfoot/), a Firefox extension that enables end-users to customize web pages and automate tasks on the Web. Won two best paper awards.",
